    "body": "I'm trying [this pdf](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1703.01161.pdf) via #8180. There is an Document Info Dict entry in this document:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPTEX.Fullbanner: \"This is pdfTeX, Version 3.14159265-2.6-1.40.17 (TeX Live 2016) kpathsea version 6.2.2\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever it is not shown inside the result of `getMetadata()`.\r\n\r\nThe problem lies within `get documentInfo()` in default `pdf.worker.js` (I don't know where these lines belong in the source, so I'm only referring to the [dist version](https://mozilla.github.io/pdf.js/build/pdf.worker.js) from the [online demo](https://mozilla.github.io/pdf.js/web/viewer.html)):\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nget documentInfo() {\r\n      var docInfo = {\r\n        PDFFormatVersion: this.pdfFormatVersion,\r\n        IsLinearized: !!this.linearization,\r\n        IsAcroFormPresent: !!this.acroForm,\r\n        IsXFAPresent: !!this.xfa\r\n      };\r\n      var infoDict;\r\n\r\n      try {\r\n        infoDict = this.xref.trailer.get('Info');\r\n      } catch (err) {\r\n        if (err instanceof _util.MissingDataException) {\r\n          throw err;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        (0, _util.info)('The document information dictionary is invalid.');\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      if ((0, _primitives.isDict)(infoDict)) {\r\n        for (var key in DocumentInfoValidators) {\r\n          if (infoDict.has(key)) {\r\n            var value = infoDict.get(key);\r\n\r\n            if (DocumentInfoValidators[key](value)) {\r\n              docInfo[key] = typeof value !== 'string' ? value : (0, _util.stringToPDFString)(value);\r\n            } else {\r\n              (0, _util.info)('Bad value in document info for \"' + key + '\"');\r\n            }\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      return (0, _util.shadow)(this, 'documentInfo', docInfo);\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd earlier in the code, `DocumentInfoValidators`:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar DocumentInfoValidators = {\r\n    Title: _util.isString,\r\n    Author: _util.isString,\r\n    Subject: _util.isString,\r\n    Keywords: _util.isString,\r\n    Creator: _util.isString,\r\n    Producer: _util.isString,\r\n    CreationDate: _util.isString,\r\n    ModDate: _util.isString,\r\n    Trapped: _primitives.isName\r\n  };\r\n```\r\n\r\nBasically, from how it's written currently, only the 4 fields plus all the *required* fields (as listed in `DocumentInfoValidators`) are outputted to the `docInfo` dictionary. Any other metadata in `infoDict` is dropped because only keys in `DocumentInfoValidators` are iterated.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, `getMetadata()` calls this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhandler.on('GetMetadata', function wphSetupGetMetadata(data) {\r\n      return Promise.all([pdfManager.ensureDoc('documentInfo'), pdfManager.ensureCatalog('metadata')]);\r\n    });\r\n```\r\n\r\n`documentInfo` is the part above, and the `metadata` here refers to the catalog dict, not the info dict:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    key: \"metadata\",\r\n    get: function get() {\r\n      var streamRef = this.catDict.getRaw('Metadata');\r\n\r\n      if (!(0, _primitives.isRef)(streamRef)) {\r\n        return (0, _util.shadow)(this, 'metadata', null);\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      var suppressEncryption = !(this.xref.encrypt && this.xref.encrypt.encryptMetadata);\r\n      var stream = this.xref.fetch(streamRef, suppressEncryption);\r\n      var metadata;\r\n\r\n      if (stream && (0, _primitives.isDict)(stream.dict)) {\r\n        var type = stream.dict.get('Type');\r\n        var subtype = stream.dict.get('Subtype');\r\n\r\n        if ((0, _primitives.isName)(type, 'Metadata') && (0, _primitives.isName)(subtype, 'XML')) {\r\n          try {\r\n            metadata = (0, _util.stringToUTF8String)((0, _util.bytesToString)(stream.getBytes()));\r\n          } catch (e) {\r\n            if (e instanceof _util.MissingDataException) {\r\n              throw e;\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            (0, _util.info)('Skipping invalid metadata.');\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      return (0, _util.shadow)(this, 'metadata', metadata);\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo this does not help either.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if this is intended or not, but a fix would be just iterate all the keys from `infoDict`. Again, I don't know if this is intended behaviour, and even if it's not, I don't know where this belongs in the source code either so I can't make a PR."
