    "body": "On some of my pdfs the files are jumping to page 2. I noticed that if I removed the zoom option that it stopped the skipping of files. I cannot see any differences between pdfs that do skip to page 2 and those that don't.\r\n\r\nAttach (recommended) or Link to PDF file here:\r\n[example-page-issue-doc.pdf](https://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js/files/2486501/example-page-issue-doc.pdf)\r\n\r\nConfiguration:\r\n- Web browser and its version: Firefox 63.0\r\n- Operating system and its version: Windows 10 Pro 1803\r\n- PDF.js version: 1.9.426\r\n- Is a browser extension: No\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce the problem:\r\n1. place the following html in a html file that is in the same directory as the web folder.\r\n`<iframe id=\"pdf-with-zoom\" frameBorder=\"0\" src=\"web/viewer.html?file=../example-page-issue-doc.pdf#zoom=page-fit&pagemode=none&page=4\" allowfullscreen height=\"100%\" width=\"49%\"></iframe>\r\n`\r\n`<iframe id=\"pdf-no-zoom\" frameBorder=\"0\" src=\"web/viewer.html?file=../example-page-issue-doc.pdf#pagemode=none&page=4\" allowfullscreen height=\"100%\" width=\"49%\"></iframe>\r\n`\r\n\r\nWhat is the expected behavior? (add screenshot)\r\nExpected behaviour is that with the zoom it displays page 4.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15227621/47074686-d58eda80-d1f2-11e8-8be6-78b6583771b7.png)\r\n\r\nWhat went wrong? (add screenshot)\r\nActually happens is that it displays page 5 but if you remove the zoom option it displays page 4.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15227621/47074713-e17a9c80-d1f2-11e8-919e-aaac30b9d680.png)\r\n"
